taunit.rl-info:
Pricking and ruling are visible;
Ruling pattern:
1A-1A-1A1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C;
Primary pricks are visible;
Ruling pricks are visible;
The upper line is written above the ruling;
The bottom line is written above the ruling.

rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra; names of the donor; 
elements of the punctuation signs;
elements of Ethiopic numbers;
the word sälam.
A few lines, divided into several groups alternating with black lines, in the pages opening the commemoration notes for each month: 
10 lines for the month of Mäggabit (fol. 7r); 
8 lines for the months of Miyazya (fol. 36r), Säne (fol. 84r) and Ḥamle (fol. 110r); 
6 lines for the months of Gǝnbot (fol. 57v), Näḥase (fol. 148v) and Ṗagwǝmen (fol. 173v).
The first two lines of the first commemoration note of the day, one (sometimes two) line of all other commemoration notes.
One line of the concluding formula for the month of Miyazya (fol. 57rc, l.1);
two lines of the concluding formula for the month of Näḥase (fol. 173rabc, ls. 12-13).

